# MagicBell - Courier
created: 2024-10-22, last updated: 2026-05-22, [Read more](https://www.courier.com/docs/external-integrations/push/magicbell)

You will need a MagicBell account with a project configured.
In Courier, navigate to the MagicBell Integration page, enter your API key and API secret, then click “Save.”
...
## ​ Overrides
Overrides can be used to change the request body that Courier uses to send a message to MagicBell.
Below is an example of overriding the Category & Action URL parameters in MagicBell:
```
{
"message": {
"template": "NOTIFICATION_TEMPLATE_ID",
"to": {
"email": "recipient@example.com"
},
"data": {},
"providers": {
"magicbell": {
"override": {
"body": {
"category": "new_message",
"action_url": "https://example.com/example_link"
}
}
}
}
}
}
```

